latestPosts.caption:
from day 0 to D-day, first people I met in blr, first friends I made in college, and proudly so, the last ones who stuck by through everything.
From @pallavigolaya sleeping on the floor just to take care of me when I was sick, to @kairasoni doing my assignments when I couldn’t meet the deadlines, to @navya.singhh waking me up everyday for IDM. I literally couldn’t have survived the last 4 years without y’all. 
You guys were the home away from home, be it 5am rides to the hospital or 5am parties, from taking trippy trips together to just sitting and sharing the deepest feelings, from fighting over 3patti to being there when hearts were broken. 

This friendship has seen a lot and survived most of it ahahah, and honestly I wouldn’t have it any other way. You guys are so weird in such weird ways, but whenever we’re chilling, there’s no one else I’d rather be with. 

From Kitty ko to Dear Donna, from Uru to Chin Lungs, I’m glad it was all with you three. 

The memories we made in the last 4 years will always be special to me, no matter whichever corner of the world you guys are in.
